Order Workflow Requirement Draft

Purpose
This document captures the current Google Sheet workflow so the project can implement the same business process correctly.

Status Model

A) Load Status (operational readiness)
- not_ready
- ready_to_pick
- picked
- complete
- trouble

B) Order Status (business and financial lifecycle)
- pending_quote
- quoted
- ordered_waiting_truck
- truck_found
- cancelled
- pod_received
- invoice_received_from_driver
- invoice_sent_to_customer (yes/no)
- customer_paid (yes/no)
- driver_paid (yes/no)

Important Business Rule
- ready_to_pick is independent from truck_found.
- In other words, "ready to pick" does not mean a truck has been found.

Workflow by Stage

1) Quote Stage (Quote tab)
- When a customer requests a quote, a row is created in the Quote tab.
- Planned quote workflow: pending_quote -> quoted -> ordered_waiting_truck.
- This stage can also confirm whether the load is ready_to_pick.
- TODO: finalize quoting requirement details.

2) Order Stage (Order tab)
- After the customer confirms the price, the order is considered confirmed.
- In the current Sheet process, column A becomes red and the row is copied to the Order tab.
- Main order progression in this stage: ordered_waiting_truck -> truck_found.
- ready_to_pick remains a separate signal and should not be used as truck_found.

3) Pickup/Delivery/POD/Invoice Stage
- After driver pickup, there is currently no explicit Sheet action for that event.
- The web application should provide tracking/confirmation for this stage.
- After delivery and POD confirmation, the row is moved to the POD tab.
- Then finance follow-up continues:
  - wait for driver POD and driver invoice
  - send invoice to customer
  - collect customer payment
  - pay the driver

Implementation Guidance for the Project
- Keep load_status and order_status as two independent tracks.
- Do not infer truck_found from ready_to_pick.
- Ensure POD/invoice/payment checkpoints are explicitly tracked in the web workflow, even if the Sheet process is currently manual for some transitions.
